# The Map — ops-manager (Cuantico Operations Manager)
*The scouted terrain of this dungeon. Read by God and every guardian.*

## Status
- [x] Session Zero complete — 2026-06-12

## Language & Tooling
- **Language**: TypeScript (ESM, `"type": "module"`)
- **Runtime**: Node.js >= 20 (`.nvmrc`)
- **Package manager**: npm workspaces (`package-lock.json`)
- **Test runner**: Vitest (`vitest.config.ts`, `tests/global-setup.ts`)
- **Linter / formatter**: ESLint 9 flat config (`eslint.config.mjs`), Prettier (`.prettierrc`)
- **Type strictness**: `tsc --noEmit` in CI; build via `tsc` → `dist/`

## Framework & Libraries
- **Primary framework**: Fastify 5 (HTTP API + webhooks), Slack Bolt 4 (Socket Mode)
- **Key libraries** (use these, don't introduce alternatives without reason):
  - `pg` — Postgres (raw SQL, no ORM)
  - `bullmq` + `ioredis` — job queue
  - `zod` — validation (skills, API contracts)
  - `pino` — logging
  - `@cuantico/contracts` — shared Zod types (`packages/contracts`)
  - LiteLLM proxy — LLM routing (`litellm-config.yaml`)
- **Frontend**: Vite + React + TS (`apps/dashboard`, workspace `@cuantico/dashboard`)
- **Explicitly banned**:
  - `BYPASS_APPROVAL=true` in production
  - Committing `.env`, Slack tokens, GHL PIT tokens, or service-account keys
  - ORM layers on top of existing raw `pg` pattern without an ADR

## Data Layer
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 16
- **Access pattern**: Raw `pg` pool (`src/lib/db/client.ts`); app role `ops_app` (limited); admin `ops` for migrations
- **Migrations location & tool**: `migrations/*.sql`, run via `npm run migrate` / `src/lib/db/migrate-cli.ts` on app boot
- **Redis**: BullMQ queues, job state

## Architecture
- **Pattern**: Monorepo — root Fastify worker/API + `packages/contracts` + `apps/dashboard`
- **Where business logic lives**: `src/skills/<domain>/`, `src/agents/`, `src/jobs/`
- **Where I/O lives**: `src/lib/*` clients (ghl, slack, db, queue, llm), `src/slack/`, `src/server.ts`
- **Source of truth doc**: `ARCHITECTURE.md` (wins over inference); phase scope in `docs/phases/PHASE-*.md`

## Infra & Deploy
- **Runtime / hosting**: Docker Compose on DigitalOcean droplet (canonical prod)
- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — lint, typecheck, test on PR/push to `main`
- **Deploy flow**: SSH → `git pull origin main` → `docker compose up -d --build` (migrations on app boot). Wrapper: `scripts/deploy.sh`
- **Local dev**: `docker compose up --build` — app on http://localhost:3100 (host) → container :3000
- **Production identifiers** (Sentinel — treat as PRODUCTION):
  - Host: `147.182.131.74` (root SSH, `/opt/ops-manager`)
  - Deploy path: `/opt/ops-manager`
  - Branch: `main`
  - Health: `http://localhost:3100/health` on droplet
  - External: `n8n.voyze.ai` (tracked workflows, read-only health checks from this service)

## House Conventions
- **Skills**: Implement `Skill` from `src/skills/_types.ts`; register in `src/server.ts`; audit via `wrap-mutation` / `audit/log.ts`
- **Mutations**: `requiresApproval` + Slack approval flow in prod; tests use `BYPASS_APPROVAL=true`
- **Naming**: kebab-case files; skill ids like `ghl.set-custom-value`
- **Error handling**: `src/lib/errors.ts` patterns; never log secrets or full transcripts in audit
- **Logging**: Pino; `LOG_LEVEL` from env

## Project-Specific Non-Negotiables
- Immutable `audit_log` — app role INSERT+SELECT only; never delete audit rows
- Human approval on every mutating skill in production (`src/lib/approval/`)
- GHL PIT tokens and roster sheets with tokens stay private; never paste token-bearing URLs in chat or commits
- Phase docs define scope — don't implement out-of-phase features without explicit user direction
- This service **operates** GHL/Assistable/n8n; it does not replace Bot Factory or customer-facing AI

